  In my case the reason was 2 fold.<br>
<br>
First, I wanted to see who bothered to actually read what I had posted and who didnt.<br>
<br>
Second, while there were close to 60 people signed up, I honestly dont know who is and isnt going to bother showing up to the raid itself.  In the past I've averaged about 50 percent attendence from sign-ups.  One raid I had 27 percent.  As such I find actual lists to be fairly time consuming for me and of little use for others.<br>
<br>
I could be wrong in this.  But I've also found that formalized lists tend to discourage people from simply showing up.  As I pointed out, with low attendence numbers we need walk-ons.  Not for the numbers of course, but for needed classes.<br>
<br>
Now one of the major disadvantages I've had is that I do not have a guild or alliance to help me in this.  Both for people and for supplemental needed classes.  This means I have to rely absolutely on those who come.  It makes more sense to me to simply record the names privately and take them first, and everyone else second.  To date I havent needed a next raid priority list since we've taken everyone who has shown up by the cut off time.  <br>
<br>
The point is, I'd like to keep these things as open and free as possible.  Whether or not this policy continues will be determined by the raiders themselves.  Should they force me to make and post seperate lists, then so be it.  But at least for this raid I was curious to see who bothered to read and who didnt.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufildiarsoulsaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fildiar Soulsaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/17/01 4:25:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I'm  sorry :(</span><hr size=1> I  had signed  up for the original fear raid the last  time before it was  cancelled. When it was postponed I figured I could  make it so  I  kept my name  on the list. But it turns out I  think ( about  90% sure on this) that I have to help someone in  RL  on Friday and  won't be able to attend. So I will take my name  off the list and let someone else take my  spot.  Goodbye, and goodluck in  Fear.<br>
